FBIS4-8911 "dreeu076_i_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-076 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Continued Serbian Offensive Reported 19 Apr Continued Serbian Offensive Reported 19 Apr `Street Fighting' Reported LD1904213794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 2103 GMT 19 Apr 94 LD1904213794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network English BFN [Text] Chaos and street fighting are raging in Gorazde. That was reported this afternoon by local official Esad Obranovic, speaking for Radio Sarajevo via ham radio operators. Obranovic said the Gorazde hospital, some 200 meters from the scene of bitter conflicts on the right bank of the River Drina, was crammed with the wounded and people were still seeking shelter in its corridors. Meanwhile, house-to-house fighting was reported in the suburbs of Gorazde. The Bosnian prime minister Haris Silajdzic said the Serb forces had hit an ammonia storage facility and were continuing to open fire on the town.
